# Environment Variables Template

## Backend (.env)
```env
# Database
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/3netra

# Authentication
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-here

# Server
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=production

# CORS (optional - defaults to allow all in development)
CORS_ORIGIN=https://www.3netraa.net
```

## Frontend (.env.local)
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-backend-url.onrender.com/api
```

## GitHub Secrets (for CI/CD)

### For Railway Deployment:
- `RAILWAY_TOKEN`: Get from Railway dashboard → Account → Tokens
- `MONGODB_URI`: Your MongoDB Atlas connection string
- `JWT_SECRET`: Same as in .env
- `MONGODB_URI_TEST`: Test database URI (optional)

### For Render Deployment:
- `RENDER_API_KEY`: Get from Render dashboard → Account → API
- `RENDER_DEPLOY_HOOK_URL`: Webhook URL from your Render service
- `MONGODB_URI`: Your MongoDB Atlas connection string
- `JWT_SECRET`: Same as in .env
- `MONGODB_URI_TEST`: Test database URI (optional)

### For GitHub Pages:
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`: Your deployed backend API URL